ANTHRAX - AUSTRALIA (05): (VICTORIA) OVINE, NEW OUTBREAKS
*********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 15 Mar 2017
Source: ABC (Australian Broadcasting Corporation) News [edited]
http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-03-15/anthrax-spreads-two-more-properties-victoria/8356456


Anthrax has been confirmed on an additional 2 farms in north-west Victoria, bringing the number of properties with livestock deaths to 4. 26 sheep have died at 2 farms near Swan Hill, with 3 of those animals testing positive for the bacteria.

The detection adds to the 2 previous confirmed deaths and more than 30 sheep that have died, but were too decomposed to test for the bacteria, at a farm at Nyah and another at Swan Hill.

Victoria's chief veterinary officer Charles Milne said he was not surprised the bacteria had been detected on other properties. He said seasonal conditions were to blame for the outbreak because the disease spread through soil, not animal to animal. We've identified another 2 infected premises. These are adjacent to an existing known infected premises," Dr Milne said. "They had boundaries that were common in one case and were very close in the other. So whilst it is a development it is not unexpected. It is entirely consistent with how we've seen this disease operate. We don't believe there's been a transportation of stock between the 2nd infected premises and the 3rd and 4th."

"Inquiries are still underway ... but we are confident no animals were moved off into the human food chain or could potentially infect other farms."

Not a quarantine failure
------------------------
Agriculture Victoria has previously stated properties surrounding confirmed anthrax sites would be vaccinated following the additional outbreak. Dr Milne said the detection of the disease on neighbouring properties was not a sign quarantine and vaccination programs had failed. "The farm that was immediately adjacent, we discovered the dead sheep when we were surveying it for vaccination," he said. "So yes, that property's been vaccinated. The other property that is a little distance away, that will be vaccinated today [15 Mar 2017]."

Dr Milne said authorities were "fully in control of this particular incident."

[Byline: Emma Brown]

